pullRequest.body:
Let `Œ¶ : C ‚•§ C` be a functor and `Œµ : ùü≠ C ‚ü∂ Œ¶` be a natural transformation. For any well-ordered type `J` such that suitable colimits exists (condition `HasIterationOfShape C J`), we define `Œ¶.transfiniteIteration Œµ J : C ‚•§ C`. In previous PR, we considered iterations of `Œ¶` to the power `j : J`. Here, we take the colimit over all `j : J`.


---

(This is WIP. The main PR is #20245.)


- [x] depends on: #19643
- [x] depends on: #19264
- [ ] depends on: #20256
